-- Mozambique Donors to Give $530 Million for Energy Projects, Noticias Says
-- B y   F r e d   K a t e r e r e
-- 2010-09-21T08:03:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-21/mozambique-donors-to-give-530-million-for-energy-projects-noticias-says.html
Mozambique’s international donors
will give the country $530 million for short- and medium-term
energy projects, Noticias reported today, citing Torvald
Akesson, Sweden’s ambassador and spokesman for the donors.  The Maputo-based state-run newspaper didn’t say when the
group, known as G19, will release the money.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Fred Katerere  in Maputo at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  